  "MeshCleanup.Manual2D.Split": {
    "prefix": "Split",
    "signature": "MeshCleanup.Manual2D.Split(crplElemEdge, dRatio=0.0, crNodeRef=None, crProjectPart=None)",
    "params": [
      "crplElemEdge",
      "dRatio=0.0",
      "crNodeRef=None",
      "crProjectPart=None"
    ],
    "text": "```python\nMeshCleanup.Manual2D.Split(crplElemEdge, dRatio=0.0, crNodeRef=None, crProjectPart=None)\n```\n\n## Description\n\nSplit the edge of an individual element into two edges at a specific ratio or at a node.\n\n## Inputs\n\n### `crplElemEdge`\n\n- A _Cursor Pair List_ specifying the element edge to be split.\n- This is a required input.\n\n### `dRatio`\n\n- A _Double_ specifying the ratio to divide element edge. The ratio is in range [0, 1]. The function will not work if the ratio value is outside this range.\n- The default value is 0.0.\n\n### `crNodeRef`\n\n- A _Cursor_ specifying the reference node that the split node will be merged into.\n- The default value is None.\n\n### `crProjectPart`\n\n- A _Cursor_ specifying the reference part to project the split node.\n- The default value is None.\n\n## Return Code\n\nA String of 1 if success, or 0 if fail.\n\n## Sample Code\n\n```psj {2-4}\nGeometry.Part.Cube(iPartColor=6409934)\nMeshCleanup.Manual2D.Split(\n        crplElemEdge=[CursorPair(Node(458), Node(467))], \n        dRatio=0.5)\n```"
  },
