    "text": "```python\nMeshEdit.MoveNode.Absolute(dDeltaX=0.0, dDeltaY=0.0, dDeltaZ=0.0, b1stCoord=True, b2ndCoord=True, b3rdCoord=True, crlNodes=[], crCoord=None)\n```\n\n## Description\n\nMove nodes to absolute coordinate values.\n\n## Inputs\n\n### `dDeltaX`\n\n- A _Double_ specifying the target coordinate value along the 1st axis.\n- The default value is 0.0.\n\n### `dDeltaY`\n\n- A _Double_ specifying the target coordinate value along the 2nd axis.\n- The default value is 0.0.\n\n### `dDeltaZ`\n\n- A _Double_ specifying the target coordinate value along the 3rd axis.\n- The default value is 0.0.\n\n### `b1stCoord`\n\n- A _Boolean_ specifying whether to move along the 1st axis.\n- The default value is True.\n\n### `b2ndCoord`\n\n- A _Boolean_ specifying whether to move along the 2nd axis.\n- The default value is True.\n\n### `b3rdCoord`\n\n- A _Boolean_ specifying whether to move along the 3rd axis.\n- The default value is True.\n\n### `crlNodes`\n\n- A _List of Cursor_ specifying the target nodes to move.\n- The default value is [].\n\n### `crCoord`\n\n- A _Cursor_ specifying the coordinate system.\n- The default value is None.\n\n## Return Code\n\nReturns a string \"1\" if successful, or \"0\" if failed.\n\n## Sample Code\n\n```psj{2}\nGeometry.Part.Cube(ilAxialNodes=[2, 2, 2], iPartColor=7463537)\nMeshEdit.MoveNode.Absolute(dDeltaX=0.015, dDeltaZ=0.01, crlNodes=[Node(6)])\n```"
